{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a4c05e8f-6085-4ff2-9c8d-81bb8734276f","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01GkNeY62xJ8kZj6oYyb3FRD","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Migrating xUnit v2 to v3"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01WKvyBsmPxkqn35ddW5FJmn","name":"bash","arguments":{"command":"cd /tmp/sv-9c448d30760641dcb8486d028ddd5c04 && dotnet nuget search xunit.v3 --take 5 2>/dev/null | head -20","description":"Search for xUnit v3 package version","initial_wait":15},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"Search for xUnit v3 package version"}],"interactionId":"0f4f5fe2-63ad-454d-b92c-b984fd48a138","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I understand the project. Let me plan the migration from xUnit.net v2 to xUnit.net v3:\n\n1. **Project file changes:**\n   - Replace `xunit` v2 package with `xunit.v3` package\n   - Remove `xunit.runner.visualstudio` (v3 doesn't need this - tests are executables)\n   - Remove `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` (v3 doesn't need this)\n   - Remove `Xunit.SkippableFact` (v3 has built-in skip support)\n   - Change SDK to `Microsoft.NET.Sdk` (keep it) or use the xUnit v3 approach\n   - Add `<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>` since v3 test projects compile as executables\n   - The target framework can stay as net8.0, though v3 requires at least .NET 6+\n\n2. **Code changes:**\n   - xUnit v3 has built-in skip support via the `Skip` parameter on attributes, so I can replace `[SkippableFact]` and `[SkippableTheory]` with regular `[Fact]` and `[Theory]` attributes, using `Assert.Skip()` for conditional skipping where needed\n   - The skip API in v3 uses `Assert.SkipWhen(condition, reason)` to skip when a condition is true and `Assert.SkipUnless(condition, reason)` to skip unless a condition is true, replacing the old `Skip.If()` and `Skip.IfNot()` patterns\n   - I need to verify the exact namespace and API surface for v3 to ensure I'm using the correct method signatures I'm second-guessing whether `Assert.SkipWhen` and `Assert.SkipUnless` actually exist in xUnit v3, so I'll stick with the safer conditional pattern using `if` statements to check the condition before calling `Assert.Skip`. For xUnit v3 with Microsoft.Testing.Platform, I need to update the global.json's test runner setting from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform instead. xUnit v3 requires the project to be an executable, so I need to update the csproj to remove the test SDK and runner packages, switch to xunit.v3, and add the Exe output type. Then in the test file, I'll replace the skippable attributes with standard Fact and Theory, and update the skip logic to use Assert.SkipUnless instead.\n\nFor the skip conditions, I need to convert Skip.If and Skip.IfNot calls to the new Assert.Skip API. I should also check what version of xunit.v3 to use—let me just try building and see what the latest available version is.","outputTokens":2193,"requestId":"480A:FBA15:3468F88:397F474:69FBF28D"},"id":"b35956b0-bc34-4e06-a296-75b15329feb9","timestamp":"2026-05-07T02:02:28.248Z","parentId":"f47ef875-39b9-4a66-a9d1-7207dd573d64"}
